      • getIssued

        public String getIssued()
        The date of listing the corresponding dataset in the catalog, as specified by dct:issued. This indicates the date of listing the dataset in the catalog and not the publication date of the dataset itself. Note DCAT standard requires dates in string format to be ISO 8601 Date and Time compliant string format i.e. "2011-12-11". In TraceProv if date format is unknown prepend it with "unparseable:" to avoid confusing it with regular dates. If date is unknown the empty string is used.
        Overrides:
        getIssued in class ADcatCatalogRecord
        See Also:
        ADcatDataset.getIssued()

      • getModified

        public String getModified()
        Most recent date on which the catalog entry was changed, updated or modified. This indicates the date of last change of a catalog entry, i.e. the catalog metadata description of the dataset, and not the date of the dataset itself. Specified by dct:modified If date is unknown the empty string is used. Note DCAT standard requires dates in string format to be ISO 8601 Date and Time compliant string format i.e. "2011-12-11". In TraceProv if date format is unknown prepend it with "unparseable:" to avoid confusing it with regular dates. If date is unknown the empty string is used.
        Overrides:
        getModified in class ADcatCatalogRecord
        See Also:
        ADcatDataset.getModified()

      • getPrimaryTopic

        @Nullable
public DcatDataset getPrimaryTopic()
        Links the catalog record to the dcat:Dataset resource described in the record. Each catalog record can have at most one primary topic i.e. describes one dataset. Specified by foaf: primaryTopic
